'''[[short]] [[form]]''' (''plural'' '''[[short forms]]''')

# A form of a word formed by [[shorten]]ing the word, usually to its first few letters or its first syllable and considered a word in its own right rather than an [[abbreviation]].
#:''"Tux" is a short form of "tuxedo"''.
#:''"Rob" is a short form of "Robert"''.<!--not a diminutive, which implies affection or smallness; "Robbie" would be a diminutive-->
# {{grammar}} Particularly in [[Slavonic]] languages: a shortened form of the [[adjective]], used [[predicatively]].
#: Example: ''[[нов]], [[нова]], [[ново]], [[новы]]'' are short forms of ''[[новый]]''.